                           [22]BooksoftheKindling

          In some parts of the earth, fireflies flash in synchrony,

                   remembering a song they heard long ago;

                     And those marked by the old magic,

                    hear the echoes of that ancient song;

                   For She who sang the song has awakened,

                  and has need of those who bear Her gifts;

                  And one by one they will answer the call,

              for – like the fireflies – they are kindled.

              The [23]Books of the Kindling tell their stories.

